<div class="dablink">For other uses, see <a href="/wiki/Risk_(disambiguation)" title="Risk (disambiguation)">Risk (disambiguation)</a>.</div>
<div class="dablink">"Risk-takers" redirects here. For the Canadian television program, see <a href="/wiki/Risk_Takers" title="Risk Takers">Risk Takers</a>.</div>
<p><b>Risk</b> is a <a href="/wiki/Concept" title="Concept">concept</a> that denotes the precise probability of specific eventualities. Technically, the notion of risk is independent from the notion of value and, as such, eventualities may have both beneficial and adverse consequences. However, in general usage the convention is to focus only on potential negative impact to some characteristic of <a href="/wiki/Value_(economics)" title="Value (economics)">value</a> that may arise from a future <a href="/wiki/Event_(probability_theory)" title="Event (probability theory)">event</a>.</p>
